   "source": [
    "# Neuro Developmental Encoding Genotype Representation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9b2ca94e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The Neuro Developmental Encoding (NDE for short) is a vector based indirect representation method to encode the genotype of **modular robot bodies** used by default in ARIEL.\n",
    "\n",
    "Source: *publication pending*"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {
    "image.png": {
     "image/png": ""
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "64a4cf72",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 1: Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "The NDEs work by passing the input vectors through a neural network, and outputting 3 adjacency probability matrices of dimensions MxM, where M denotes the number of robot modules we want to generate. An adjacency matrix encodes the probability of a connection between two modules.\n",
    "\n",
    "The three adjacency matrices are:\n",
    "* The *type* matrix holds the probabilities of a specific module being of **hinge** or **brick**,\n",
    "* The *connection* matrix holds the probabilities of two modules being connected, for each of the 6 face of the module \n",
    "* The *rotation* matrix contains the probabilities of a connected module being rotated. \n",
    "    * The possible rotation are: 45, 90, 135, 180 and 225.\n",
    "    * Note that 2 hinges connected to each other can only be rotated on 90 degree increments\n",
    "\n",
    "The evolvable/learnable genotype is in the form of a list of vectors as seen in the figure below.\n",
    "\n",
    "![image.png](attachment:image.png)\n",
    "\n",
    "For more information, please read the published paper (pending).\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4aa2d892",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 2: Implementation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9dda8c09",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Needed Imports"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 116,
   "id": "ea44f98b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# NDE imports\n",
    "from ariel.ec.genotypes.nde import NeuralDevelopmentalEncoding\n",
    "from ariel.body_phenotypes.robogen_lite.constructor import (\n",
    "    construct_mjspec_from_graph,\n",
    ")\n",
    "from ariel.body_phenotypes.robogen_lite.decoders.hi_prob_decoding import (\n",
    "    HighProbabilityDecoder\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Robot visualisation\n",
    "from ariel.simulation.environments import SimpleFlatWorld\n",
    "from ariel.utils.renderers import single_frame_renderer\n",
    "import mujoco as mj\n",
    "\n",
    "# Imports for generating numbers\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualising Matrices\n",
    "from plotting import plot_matrices"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "591dabd0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Initialisation\n",
    "\n",
    "The NDE requires 2 parameters to be initialised. \n",
    "1. The number of ARIEL Modules it is encoding for, and \n",
    "2. The size of the vectors used in the genotype. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 117,
   "id": "c3935398",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define number of modules and gene_size\n",
    "num_modules = 20\n",
    "\n",
    "# Default value is 64, but we will use 8 for easier visualisation\n",
    "gene_size = 8\n",
    "\n",
    "NDE = NeuralDevelopmentalEncoding(number_of_modules = num_modules,\n",
    "                                  genotype_size = gene_size\n",
    "                                  )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ffc098e0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Generate Random Genotype"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 118,
   "id": "17989e8e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[[-18.581  16.084  90.367 -59.906 -24.356   3.947 -35.631  95.090]\n",
      " [-42.613   4.969  24.225 -33.693 -81.706 112.593  34.475 -18.033]\n",
      " [140.321  70.105 -44.490 -24.584  64.774 -16.026 -89.251  96.836]]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Random genotype of shape (3, gene_size)\n",
    "# The scale of the values in the vector can affect the diversity of the generated genotypes.\n",
    "# You can find a detailed breakdown of the scale values in the `tests/functional/nde.ipynb` file.\n",
    "scale = 64\n",
    "example_gene = np.random.normal(loc=0,\n",
    "                                scale=scale,\n",
    "                                size=(3, gene_size)) \n",
    "\n",
    "print(example_gene)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "10cf6e53",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Generate matrices"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 119,
   "id": "77aaa59d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "matrices = NDE.forward(example_gene)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 120,
   "id": "7c3eb977",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(20, 4)\n",
      "(20, 20, 6)\n",
      "(20, 8)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(matrices[0].shape)\n",
    "print(matrices[1].shape)\n",
    "print(matrices[2].shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 121,
   "id": "7b8d79f5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 700x300 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 900x600 with 12 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot_matrices(matrices)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c6354cbf",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 3: Robot Graph\n",
    "\n",
    "NDEs were designed to primarily function as a modular robot genotype. The probability matrices don't really have many other uses (directly). So by default, ARIEL contains functions to turn the NDE genotype into a robot graph.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 122,
   "id": "47978b5d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Get robot graph from matrices and construct robot specification\n",
    "def matrices_to_robot(p_matrices, num_modules):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Create mujoco specification from robot genotype\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Decode the high-probability graph\n",
    "    hpd = HighProbabilityDecoder(num_modules)\n",
    "    robot_graph = hpd.probability_matrices_to_graph(\n",
    "        p_matrices[0],\n",
    "        p_matrices[1],\n",
    "        p_matrices[2],\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    robot_spec = construct_mjspec_from_graph(robot_graph)\n",
    "    return robot_spec.spec\n",
    "\n",
    "robot_spec = matrices_to_robot(matrices, num_modules)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2374657b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Spawn robot in simulation\n",
    "Now that we have the robot specification, we can spawn the robot in a world and visualise it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 123,
   "id": "46ff41c7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=480x640>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 123,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Initialise the world you want to spawn the robot in\n",
    "world = SimpleFlatWorld()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Spawn the robot\n",
    "world.spawn(robot_spec)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialise mujoco model and data\n",
    "model = world.spec.compile()\n",
    "data = mj.MjData(model)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Render a frame of the robot\n",
    "# Zoomed in for better viewing\n",
    "single_frame_renderer(model, \n",
    "                      data,\n",
    "                      cam_fovy=2,\n",
    "                      cam_pos=[-0.7,    # x pos\n",
    "                               0.1,       # y pos\n",
    "                               0.5],    # z pos\n",
    "                      )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "28daf780",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 4: Evolutionary Operators\n",
    "\n",
    "Since the NDES are vector based, any vector crossover and mutation method works on them.\n",
    "\n",
    "Crossover:\n",
    "* One-Point\n",
    "* N-Point\n",
    "* Uniform\n",
    "* etc\n",
    "\n",
    "Mutation:\n",
    "* Swap \n",
    "* Gaussian\n",
    "* Shuffle \n",
    "* etc\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "One rule to keep in mind is to not mix the input vectors when doing these operations. This can be seen in the example figure below."
   ]
  },
